The paper deals with image steganography, which involves hiding information in images. This falls under the broad category of multimedia (cs.MM) and security and privacy (cs.CR). The paper specifically uses color images and the Hue-Saturation-Intensity (HSI) color model, which are topics related to computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR), which is a metric commonly used in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG).
